{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyO8feIZOoi2Fkgcc4iMcnkW"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Goal: To solve the XOR problem using MLP\n","- MLP can deal with linearly inseparable data\n","- MLP has atleast one hidden layer other than the output layer\n","- Same SLP architecture with some hidden layers b/w input & output layers\n","\n","> **Methods to solve**\n","\n","$$\n","\\boxed{\n","\\begin{array}{|c|c|c|}\n","\\hline\n","\\textbf{Batch Size} & \\textbf{Number of Batches} & \\textbf{Training Type} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","1 & 4 & \\text{Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","2 & 2 & \\text{Mini-batch Gradient Descent} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","4 & 1 & \\text{Batch Gradient Descent} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\end{array}\n","}\n","$$\n","\n","> **Truth table**\n","\n","$$\n","\\boxed{\n","\\begin{array}{|c|c|c|}\n","\\hline\n","\\hspace{8pt}x_1\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}x_2\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}y\\hspace{8pt} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}1\\hspace{8pt} & \\hspace{8pt}0\\hspace{8pt} \\\\\n","\\hline\n","\\end{array}\n","}\n","$$\n","\n","**We will use batch gradient descent**"],"metadata":{"id":"_1PI1Wf3o2Tn"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Architecture\n","- XOR Formula:\n","$$x_{1} \\oplus x_{2} = x_{1}\\overline{x_{2}} + \\overline{x_{1}}x_{2}$$\n","\n","- Layer 0 (input layer) (2 inputs)\n","\n","- Layer 1 (hidden layer) (2 inputs & 2 outputs)\n","  - Neuron 1\n","  - Neuron 2\n","\n","`{no calc is needed b/w outputs of both neurons, b'cos, output layer needs both of those as input}`\n","\n","- Layer 2 (output layer) (2 inputs & 1 output)\n","  - Neuron 1"],"metadata":{"id":"A45a6iWlo8Ym"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Implementation (1 hidden layer, no batches)"],"metadata":{"id":"lLGdKvqixZne"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Importing required libraries**"],"metadata":{"id":"wpHtzdwlxt37"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"EOokRmmooUdC"},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Training - input data (Input matrix) (I) [4 x 2]**"],"metadata":{"id":"SSe-lN5ax8yE"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["I = np.array([\n","    [0, 0],\n","    [0, 1],\n","    [1, 0],\n","    [1, 1]\n","])"],"metadata":{"id":"C_zsh4Rmx5KH"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Training - target data (Ground Truth matrix) (Y) (1 x 4)**"],"metadata":{"id":"yZav_GgizmA-"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["Y = np.array([0, 1, 1, 0])\n","Y = Y.reshape(4, 1)"],"metadata":{"id":"mldtt7E5zjKk"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Defining hyper parameters**"],"metadata":{"id":"CN0FNYKEz8fZ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# learning rate\n","\n","lr = 1.5\n","\n","# no of cycles\n","\n","epoch = 1200"],"metadata":{"id":"Sl4a-IFaz7Ia"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Sigmoid function**"],"metadata":{"id":"GQD7dXIe3ith"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def sigmoid(x):\n","  return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-x))"],"metadata":{"id":"bIsZl-lz3lsR"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Sigmoid differentiation**"],"metadata":{"id":"6TyLE4KVjCtx"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def sigmoid_derivative(x):\n","  return sigmoid(x) * (1 - sigmoid(x))"],"metadata":{"id":"XwDsi3LjjHmB"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **SLP computation function**"],"metadata":{"id":"7-mo-GhG2zYo"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def SLP(I, W, b):\n","  return sigmoid(np.dot(I, W) + b)"],"metadata":{"id":"l2iD0DyE2cfa"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **New weight and bias matrix (includes error calculation)**\n"],"metadata":{"id":"LzDZrvuNpBJu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def new_weight_bias(I, P, Y, w2, b2, A1, w1, b1, lr):\n","\n","  # calculating mean standard error - mse (output layer)\n","\n","  mse = np.mean((P - Y) ** 2)\n","\n","  ## Back propagation\n","  # calculating delta2 - error in output layer\n","\n","  delta2 = (2 / I.shape[0]) * (P - Y) * sigmoid_derivative(np.dot(A1, w2) + b2)\n","\n","  # calculating delta1 - error in layer 1 (hidden layer)\n","\n","  delta1 = np.dot(delta2, w2.T) * sigmoid_derivative(np.dot(I, w1) + b1)\n","\n","  # output layer gradients (weight & bias gradients)\n","\n","  dw2 = np.dot(A1.T, delta2)\n","  db2 = np.sum(delta2, axis=0)\n","\n","  # hidden layer gradients (weight & bias gradients)\n","\n","  dw1 = np.dot(I.T, delta1)\n","  db1 = np.sum(delta1, axis=0)\n","\n","  # updating weights and bias\n","\n","  return (w2 - lr * dw2), (b2 - lr * db2), (w1 - lr * dw1), (b1 - lr * db1), mse"],"metadata":{"id":"g5dz5vWmpVur"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["> **Training the AI model to predict Y**"],"metadata":{"id":"1bPMWdz146tb"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["### weight and bias initiation\n","\n","## =============== Layer 1 (2 neurons -> 2 weight columns)\n","\n","# weight matrix\n","\n","w1 = np.random.randn(2, 2)     # it is 2 x 2 and not 2 x 1 as usual. B'cos, there are 2 neurons in this layer\n","\n","# bias vector (collection of 2 bias values for the 2 neurons)\n","\n","b1 = np.random.randn(1, 2)     # it is 1 x 2 and not 1 x 1 as usual. B'cos, there are 2 neurons in this layer\n","\n","## ================ Layer 2 (2 neurons) (2 outputs of layer 1 as a single matrix recieved as inputs)\n","\n","# weight matrix\n","\n","w2 = np.random.randn(2, 1)      # only 1 neuron\n","\n","# bias vector\n","\n","b2 = np.random.randn(1, 1)      # only 1 neuron\n","\n","## ================= Actual training begins\n","\n","for i in range(epoch):\n","\n","  print(f\"Epoch: {i + 1}\")\n","\n","  # calculating activation matrix of layer 1 (hidden layer)\n","\n","  A1 = SLP(I, w1, b1)\n","\n","  # calculating prediction matrix / activation matrix of layer 2 (output layer)\n","\n","  prediction_matrix = SLP(A1, w2, b2)\n","\n","  # printing ground truth matrix\n","\n","  print(\"\\nGround Truth matrix:\\n\")\n","  print(Y)\n","\n","  # printing prediction matrix\n","\n","  print(\"\\nPrediction matrix:\\n\")\n","  print(prediction_matrix)\n","\n","  # calculating new weights and biases\n","\n","  w2, b2, w1, b1, mse = new_weight_bias(I, prediction_matrix, Y, w2, b2, A1, w1, b1, lr)\n","\n","  # printing mse\n","\n","  print(f\"\\nMSE: {mse}\")"],"metadata":{"id":"a68Adqc54MSm","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781763807102,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":759,"user":{"displayName":"bbr2007","userId":"03194248298110772959"}},"outputId":"f8dd6352-9d0f-49dc-81ad-7cc9e61bab70"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\u001b[1;30;43mStreaming output truncated to the last 5000 lines.\u001b[0m\n","\n","MSE: 0.006586980709732656\n","Epoch: 907\n","\n","Ground Truth matrix:\n","\n","[[0]\n"," [1]\n"," [1]\n"," [0]]\n","\n","Prediction matrix:\n","\n","[[0.07873169]\n"," [0.91348873]\n"," [0.91237471]\n"," [0.07028782]]\n","\n","MSE: 0.006575361927857543\n","Epoch: 908\n","\n","Ground Truth matrix:\n","\n","[[0]\n"," [1]\n"," [1]\n"," [0]]\n","\n","Prediction matrix:\n","\n","[[0.07866154]\n"," [0.91356395]\n"," [0.91245229]\n"," [0.07022603]]\n","\n","MSE: 0.006563781301121915\n","Epoch: 909\n","\n","Ground Truth matrix:\n","\n","[[0]\n"," [1]\n"," [1]\n"," [0]]\n","\n","Prediction matrix:\n","\n","[[0